You are a senior full-stack engineer working on the sharqaljazeera-website built with Next.js 15 (App Router), TailwindCSS 4, Drizzle ORM + PostgreSQL, and Better Auth for authentication. The app uses TypeScript, Lucide React icons, and follows a clean, modular architecture.

## Objective

Build a News page (/news) that publicly displays all admin-created news posts as responsive cards, each showing an image, date, title, and text preview.

## Structure

Framework: Next.js 15 with App Router

Styling: TailwindCSS 4

Database: PostgreSQL via Drizzle ORM

ORM: Drizzle ORM

Auth: Better Auth (only admins can manage news)

Language: TypeScript

Icons: Lucide React

## Tasks

Database Setup (Drizzle ORM)

Create a news table with fields:

id (UUID, primary key)

title (string, max 200 chars)

text (text)

imageUrl (string)

date (timestamp with timezone, defaults to now)

authorId (UUID) — references users.id

Migrate using Drizzle (db:generate, db:push).

Admin Management (Server Only)

Create admin-only functions (in src/lib/admin/news.ts) to:

Add new news entries

Edit or delete existing news entries

These should be server actions protected by Better Auth admin validation (e.g., session.user.role === 'admin').

There is no public form for creating or editing news.

Public Page Setup

Create /app/news/page.tsx to:

Fetch all news posts from the database (ordered by date DESC).

Pass them to a NewsCard component for rendering.

This page is publicly accessible.

Component Creation

Create a NewsCard component (src/components/NewsCard.tsx) with props:

{
title: string;
text: string;
imageUrl: string;
date: string;
}

Display image, formatted date, title, and truncated text.

Use TailwindCSS for clean responsive styling.

## Output Requirements

Return:

The Drizzle schema for news

The NewsCard React component

The Next.js News page (/app/news/page.tsx)

The admin-only functions (src/lib/admin/news.ts)

Instructions on where to place each file and how to restrict admin access using Better Auth

## Notes

Only admins can create or modify news posts — public users can only read.

Use server-only and auth() checks for admin routes/actions.

Optimize images using Next.js <Image />.

Keep UI minimal and mobile-friendly.

Maintain consistent folder structure with src/components, src/app/news, and src/lib/db.
